<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Initial Prefectural Government Budgets Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Initial Prefectural Government Budgets Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1504083994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0805 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1504083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, April 15 KYODO -- Initial fiscal 1994 
budgets of prefectural governments nationwide, including the 
Tokyo Metropolitan Government, totaled 48,371.1 billion yen, up 
3.0 percent from the previous year, the Home Affairs Ministry 
said Friday [15 April]. 
  The growth rate for prefectural budgets for the year that 
started on April 1, excluding the budgets of Ishikawa, Kyoto and 
Nagasaki prefectures, was 3.4 percent, compared with 3.7 percent 
for the national government's local fiscal program for the year. 
  The three prefectures had compiled only minimal budgets due 
to their gubernatorial elections. 
  In the prefectural budgets, excluding those of the three 
prefectures, public works projects financed by local governments 
alone were expanded 10.0 percent from the previous year to help 
stimulate the economy. 
  The rate was lower than the 12.0 percent growth rate for the 
fiscal 1994 local fiscal program. 

</TEXT>

