<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Minister Comments on GATT Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Minister Comments on GATT Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1504090094 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0600 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1504090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Trade Minister Satrio Budiarjo Yudono has told 
newsmen in Jakarta that Indonesia hopes all developed countries 
will be united in observing the agreement on liberal, fair, and 
non-discriminative international trade based on the GATT 
framework. 
  He said that following the signing of the final act of the 
Uruguay Round trade talks, Indonesia and other developing 
countries hoped their export products could gain more market 
access in the developed countries. 
  According to the minister, it is important for developed 
countries to open their markets to goods from developing 
countries considering that Indonesia, one of the developing 
countries, had already adopted a liberal trade policy in line 
with the outcome of the Uruguay Round talks. He said that apart 
from that, the developed countries should provide technical 
assistance to developing countries instead of attaching other 
conditional clauses to the trade agreement. 
  It is hoped that the Uruguay Round trade talks on textiles 
and agriculture could create a trade policy that is not 
contradictory to the agreement reached at Uruguay Round talks 
and that trade discrimination against developing countries will 
be eliminated. 

</TEXT>

