<F P=106> [YONHAP from Washington] </F>
  [Text] North Korea hopes to resume dialogue with the 
United States, CNN TV reported today in a Pyongyang-datelined 
story. 
  In a live report via telephone from Pyongyang during "Larry 
King Live" program, Chinoy, a Beijing-based CNN TV correspondent 
who is now in Pyongyang, said that North Korea desperately hopes 
[kalmanghada] to have high-level talks with the United States 
and that President Kim Il-song seeks a U.S. figure who would 
listen to his views regarding the nuclear issue. 
  Evangelist Billy Graham, who appeared in the program, said 
that he had a three-hour-long talk with President Kim during his 
recent visit to Pyongyang and, on this basis, expressed an 
upbeat view on the smooth solution of the nuclear problem. He 
confirmed that he had delivered President Kim's reply to the 
White House. However, he declined to give the specific contents 
of the reply. 

