<DOCNO> FBIS4-5900 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas073_d_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-073 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK `Reinforced' PRC, Russia Border Guards </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK `Reinforced' PRC, Russia Border Guards </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1504115894 Seoul YONHAP in English 1135 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1504115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 15 (YONHAP) -- Amid reports of a stream 
of North Korean people escaping from their communist country or 
from their logging yards in Siberia, North Korea has sharply 
reinforced border guards in areas bordering China and Russia, it 
was learned here on Friday. 
  "The brigade-strength North Korean border troops have 
recently been reinforced to the strength of a corps consisting 
of 30,000 to 40,000 men," Vice Unification Minister Song 
Yong-tae said. 
  Speaking at a panel talks at the National Assembly, Song 
said 
in the past loggers at North Korea-run logging yards in Siberia 
used to be granted special outings on Kim Il-song's birthday, 
April 15, the biggest public holiday of North Korea. 
  "We have a report indicating that this year no outings were 
allowed at all for their loggers in Siberia," Song said. 
  He said there had been no particular signs of armed 
provocation on the part of North Korea. 
  But, people there have lately been whipped into producing 
more military supplies in addition to daily necessities, and Kim 
Il- song's birthday is being observed in low-key celebrations 
this year, Song said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

