<H3> <TI>   Secretary Perry's Visit to Seoul `Delayed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Secretary Perry's Visit to Seoul `Delayed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1504001694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0010 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1504001694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington, April 15 (YONHAP) -- Secretary of 
Defense William Perry has delayed his April 17-19 visit to 
Seoul, citing the shooting down Thursday of two U.S. helicopters 
in northern Iraq by American fighters, diplomatic sources here 
said. 
  Perry, who was scheduled to leave for Tokyo and Seoul Friday 
to discuss the North Korean nuclear crisis, decided to postpone 
his trip because of the tragedy in which American F-15 fighters 
enforcing the "no-fly" zone over northern Iraq mistakenly shot 
down two U.S. Army choppers, killing more than 20 people, the 
sources said. 
  The Department of Defense notified the South Korean Embassy 
here of the delay, saying Perry's visit to Seoul will be 
rescheduled next week when the downing is cleared up, they said. 
The diplomatic sources, however, did not rule out the 
possibility that the visit could be delayed for a longer period 
if the mishap triggered a political and military uproar in and 
outside the United States. 
  The U.S. defense secretary was scheduled to meet with his 
South Korean counterpart Yi Pyong-tae to tackle the North Korean 
nuclear problem in Seoul from April 17-19. 

</TEXT>

