<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Plans Officers Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Plans Officers Reshuffle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1504025894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0204 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1504025894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 15 (YONHAP) -- The Defense Ministry 
will announce over the weekend a reshuffle of Army and Air Force 
officers affecting eight to 10 Army two- and three-star 
officers, informed sources said Friday. 
  The first military personnel changes by Defense Minister Yi 
Pyong-tae, the Army reshuffle will likely involve the discharge 
of three- and four-star generals who were members of the defunct 
Hana- hoe, a private politically motivated club of some Korean 
military academy-graduated officers once led by Former 
Presidents Chon Tu- hwan and No Tae-u. 
  Of the one- and two-star Hana-hoe members, some major 
generals will be discharged from active service and the 
remaining major and brigadier generals will be dismissed from 
important staff and division command posts. 
  The scope of the Army reshuffle will depend on whether Gen. 
Kim Chae-chang, deputy commander of the combined ROK-U.S. Forces 
Command, is discharged for his links with Hana-hoe, the sources 
said. 

</TEXT>

