<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Delegation Holds Talks in Beijing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Delegation Holds Talks in Beijing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1504092894 Hanoi VNA in English 0655 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1504092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 15 -- A high-level military 
delegation led by Senior Lieutenant Gen. Dao Dinh Luyen, member 
of the party Central Committee, vice minister of defence and 
chief of the General Staff of the Vietnam People's Army, has 
been in China for an official friendship visit since April 9. 
The visit was made at the invitation of the chief of the 
General Staff of the People's Liberation Army of China. The 
Vietnamese delegation held talks on April 10 with a Chinese 
military delegation led by Sr. Lt. Gen Chi Haotian, chief of the 
General Staff of the People's Liberation Army of China. The two 
sides informed each other of the economic construction and 
military activities in their countries and unanimously agreed to 
continue strengthening the time-honoured friendship between the 
peoples and armies of Vietnam and China. The delegation was 
received on the same day by Liu Huaqing, permanent member of the 
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China Central 
Committee and deputy head of its Military Commission. It was 
also received by Qiao Shi, permanent member of the Communist 
Party of China's Political Bureau and chairman of the Standing 
Committee of the National People's Congress of China of the 
Communist Party of China Central Committee and deputy head of 
its Military Commission. [sentence as received] 
  It called on the Chairman Mao Memorial Hall, laid a flower 
wreath to the Monument to the People's Heroes in the Tiananmen 
Square, and visited the College of National Defence. On April 
12, the delegation left Beijing for a tour of various localities 
in China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

