<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Messages of greetings 
were sent to the great leader President Kim Il-song by heads of 
state and party leaders of different countries on the occasion 
of his birthday. 
  The messages came from Ugandan President Yoweri Kaguta 
Museveni, Tanzanian President Ali Hassan Mwinyi, Burkinabe 
president, head of state and President of the Council of 
Ministers Blaise Compaore, General Secretary of the Party of 
Revolution of Benin Ali Houdou, chairman of the C.C. [Central 
Committee], the Burundi Party of Unity for National Progress 
Nicolas Mayugi and acting leader of the February 18th Movement 
of Trinidad and Tobago Vincent Cabrea. 
  The messages extend warmest greetings to President Kim 
Il-song and wish him good health and long life. 
  They express firm solidarity with the Workers' Party of 
Korea 
and the Korean people in their efforts for the independent and 
peaceful reunification of Korea. 

</TEXT>

