for National Reunification in Germany, and his party and Rev. 
Cho Tok- chon, director of the Korea Institute of William Carey 
University, the U.S. 
  Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of 
Korea Kim Yong-sun and officials concerned were present. 
  The congratulatory groups, delegations and overseas Koreans 
presented floral baskets to President Kim Il-song on his 
birthday and wished him good health and a long life. 
  President Kim Il-song expressed thanks for this and had a 
talk with them in a cordial atmosphere overflowing with 
compatriotic feelings. 

</TEXT>

