<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senior Officials at Film Showing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senior Officials at Film Showing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1504051194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0453 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1504051194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Senior party and 
government officials Thursday appreciated the 17th part of the 
multi-part feature film "The Nation and Destiny" which has been 
released on the occasion of the April fete. 
  Appreciating the film were Kang Song-san, Pak Song-chol, Kim 
Yong-chu and other senior party and government officials, Yi 
Chin- kyu, first vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee 
of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan 
(Chongnyon) who is heading a congratulatory group of Korean 
residents from Japan participating in the April 15 celebrations, 
and members of congratulatory groups, delegations and visiting 
groups of Koreans overseas from various regions. 
  The 17th part of "The Nation and Destiny" which has been 
completed as another masterpiece under the energetic guidance of 
the party is based on the life of Ho Chong-suk who was intensely 
loyal to the party and the leader till her last moments. 
  Through the chequered destiny and mental development of the 
heroine who joined in the communist movement in the 1920s when 
she was still a girl, the film shows in a profound artistic 
depiction the truth that one can not fight a worthy struggle to 
save the destiny of the motherland and the nation when one is 
not guided by a sagacious leader. 

</TEXT>

