<H3> <TI>   Kim Ik-hyon Appointed KPA Vice Marshal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Ik-hyon Appointed KPA Vice Marshal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1504103194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1019 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1504103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- A decision of the 
Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK], the 
Central Military Commission of the WPK, the National Defence 
Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the 
Central People's Committee of the DPRK on awarding the rank of 
vice marshal of the Korean People's Army to Comrade Kim Ik-hyon 
has been adopted. 
  The decision dated April 15 says that it has been decided to 
award the rank of vice marshal of the Korean People's Army to 
Comrade Kim Ik-hyon who fought devotedly with arms in his hands 
from the first days of the Korean revolution for the motherland 
and the people in the anti-Japanese revolutionary war to defeat 
the Japanese imperialists and in the great fatherland liberation 
war for routing the U.S. imperialist aggressors, holding the 
great leader Comrade Kim Il-song in high esteem as the centre of 
unity, and has devoted his whole life to strengthening the 
people's Armed Forces, defending Comrade Kim Il-song and the 
party with arms. 

</TEXT>

