<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unity Between Leader, People Described </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unity Between Leader, People Described </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1504052694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0504 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1504052694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Korean Revolution With Leader and People in Perfect </F>
Harmony Will Be Ever-victorious" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
describes the unity of the leader and the people in harmonious 
whole as the greatest gain of the Korean revolution and the 
source of the invincible might of Korean-style socialism. 
  The paper in an editorial dedicated to the birthday of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song stresses that the whole 
history of the Korean revolution is proud annals which have seen 
the achievement of the perfect unity between the leader and the 
revolutionary soldiers, between the leader and the people and 
victorious advance of the revolution based on its might. 
  The dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il is quoted as saying: 
  "Since the dawn of our revolution, the Korean communists 
have 
been convinced that they could carve out the thorny 
revolutionary road only under the leadership of the great 
Comrade Kim Il-song, and have won victories, enduring all 
ordeals, and lived and fought with everlasting, single-hearted 
loyalty to him, entrusting their destinies entirely to him." 
  The editorial continues: 
  Since the beginning of his revolutionary activities, the 
great leader Comrade Kim Il-song has always believed in the 
people and found himself among them in leading the revolution, 
unreservedly displaying the qualities and traits of a great 
leader of the people. 
  The great leader believes in the people and the latter trust 
and follow him. The bonds between them are those of kinship 
between the father and his children; they are so unbreakable 
that they can withstand any storm and stress and accomplish 
anything. Thus, the Korean revolution began with the harmonious 
unity between the leader and the people and has traversed a 
brilliant course on the basis of its might. 
  The perfect unity between the leader and the people is a 
mighty strength in resolutely defending the cause of 
Korean-style socialism. 
  The might of perfect unity between the leader and the people 
is fully demonstrated in the Korean revolution because it is one 
living body of common destiny and an integral whole in ideology 
and purpose. 
  He has always sincerely trusted the revolutionary soldiers 
and people and regarded their destiny as his own, while the 
people have absolutely trusted him as the centre and top brain 
of their lives and resolutely defended him. 
  Still today he is leading the people along the road of 
socialism, unswervingly assuming responsibility for their 
destiny, and the people are entrusting their destiny to the 
party and the leader and fighting with the unshakable resolve to 
follow them forever. 
  Our people have staunchly fought, taking the immortal chuche 
idea as their unshakable faith and the only banner of unity 
since the great leader founded this revolutionary idea. 
  The unity of our people in ideology and purpose is growing 
stronger because the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il is 
constantly developing the chuche idea to perfection. 
  The perfect unity between the leader and the people is 
mighty 
because it is being carried forward and consolidated through 
generations for the accomplishment of the cause of socialism. 
  The vigorous advance of the whole party, the entire people 
and the whole army closely united behind the dear leader shows 
that the harmonious unity between the leader and the people, 
which has been formed and consolidated through history, is being 
successfully carried forward with eternal vitality. 
  The source of the solidity of our perfect harmony is the 
great leader's idea of "believing in the people as in heaven." 
Our perfect harmony based on this great idea will never be 
broken. 
  The integral whole of the leader, the party and the people 
has been, is and will remain the lifeline of our socialism and 
the all- conquering banner. 
  We must make the advance of our revolution a history of the 
most tight bonds of kinship between the leader and the people, 
between the leader and the soldiers in the future, too. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

