BFN 

  [Text] A ceremony to sign a trilateral agreement between 
the Governments of the Union of Myanmar [Burma], the People's 
Republic of China [PRC], and the Lao People's Democratic 
Republic [LPDR] on the PRC-LPDR-Myanmar border tri-junction 
point was held today at the Foreign Ministry Annex Building in 
Yangon [Rangoon]. 
  U Aye Lwin, director general of Consular Affairs, 
International Treaties, and Research Department of the Ministry 
of Foreign Affairs; Mr. Liang Feng, ambassador of PRC, and Mr. 
Kideng Thammavong, ambassador of Laos, signed the agreement on 
behalf of their respective governments. 

