<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Considers Expanding Coalition Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hosokawa Considers Expanding Coalition Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304143194 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 13 Apr 94 
Morning Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1304143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 12 April, Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa 
discussed with Muneaki Samejima, deputy chief secretary of the 
Japan New Party, the issue of expanding parliamentary group 
"Kaikaku [Reform]" to include other political forces. During 
the discussions at the prime minister's official residence, he 
said: "It is important for the ruling coalition to go back to 
the spirit in which they started out and maintain the current 
framework. On the other hand, it is also necessary to invite 
other political forces to the ruling coalition." In this way he 
indicated that, based on the current formation of seven 
political parties and one parliamentary group, the ruling 
coalition should establish a new framework by inviting some 
Liberal Democratic Party members. 

</TEXT>

