<H3> <TI>   Australia's Bill Hayden Begins Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Australia's Bill Hayden Begins Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Guest of Honor at Dinner </H4>

<F P=102> OW1504182794 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1444 GMT 15 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1504182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- "Your 
visit is opening a new page in the history of 
Mongolian-Australian relations and I am sure that it would be of 
great value in the development of bilateral relations the 
government and the people of Mongolia are grateful that 
Australia since the very beginning has been steadily supporting 
the democratic renovations in Mongolia, said the President of 
Mongolia P. Ochirbat at the dinner given in honour of the 
Governor General of Australia Bill Hayden staying here on an 
official visit. [no closing quotation marks as received] 
  In his speech Bill Hayden said that the present visit gives 
him an opportunity to express on behalf of the Australian people 
to all the Mongolians the best wishes for success in the 
political and economic spheres. Australia has been persistently 
supporting the processes of democratization started in Mongolia 
since the disintegration of the Soviet Union. Australia 
respects the establishing of the democratic Mongolian nation. 
  The heads of the two countries have exchanged opinions on 
the 
possibilities of developing cooperation including the issues of 
attracting the Australian investment into the Mongolian economy, 
processing of raw materials of the country, introducing the 
experience of Australia on keeping an extensive cattle breeding, 
developing infrastructure in the countryside and etc. 

</TEXT>

