<H4>    Holds News Conference </H4>

<F P=102> OW1604142994 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1206 GMT 16 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1604142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 16 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Staying 
here on an official visit at the invitation of the President of 
Mongolia the Governor General of Australia B. Hayden has met 
today with newsmen. During the meeting B. Hayden has noted the 
fruitful cooperation of the two countries and the opportunities 
available for its furthering as well. He pointed out in his 
speech that Australia actively takes part in the activities of 
the countries rendering assistance and support to Mongolia and 
said that the Government of Australia is interested in the 
cooperation with Mongolia in the sphere of agriculture, mining 
industry and use of natural resources of Mongolia. B. Hayden 
noted that as a country pertaining to the Asian and Pacific 
region Australia has been paying much attention to the 
development of its relations with the countries of the region. 
The honoured guest also gave answers to the questions of 
interest for newsmen. 

</TEXT>

