<H3> <TI>   Hural Members Urged To Cease Political Disputes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hural Members Urged To Cease Political Disputes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304161094 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1327 GMT 13 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1304161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 13 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The United 
Party for Mongolian Traditions has issued a statement addressing 
the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party (MPRP), the National 
Democratic Party and the Social Democratic Party. The statement 
draws their attention to the necessity for extracting lessons 
from the past reminding that frequently the struggle between the 
state officials for power and privileges was serving to the 
interests of alien conquerors. On behalf of its membership the 
United Party for Supporting the Mongolian Traditions has called 
upon the members of the Great State Hural to cease the political 
argues and disputes and unify their efforts in order to justify 
their voters' confidence in the common interests of Mongolia. 

</TEXT>

