<H3> <TI>   Hunger Strikers Seek Government Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hunger Strikers Seek Government Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    MDA Activists Begin Strike </H4>

<F P=102> OW1304161294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1346 GMT 13 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1304161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 13 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Ten 
activists of the Mongolian Democratic Association (MDA) have 
gone on a political hunger strike at the central square of the 
capital. 
  The MDA who was the first to appear on the political scene 
has resorted to the experienced method of pressing the 
authorities after nearly a one-month demands to the government 
for its resignation. Four years ago the MDA by means of hunger 
strike forced the then political leadership of the country the 
Political Bureau of the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party 
(MPRP) to resign. 
  Prior to going on the hunger strike a rally of supporters of 
the MDA has been held at the square during which the demands for 
resignation of the government headed by the Premier P. Jasray 
were reiterated. About 8 thousand people participated in the 
rally in spite of the fact that the city authorities have not 
permitted to hold an action on the main square of the country. 
  The democratic forces believe that the present government 
has 
failed to cope with the major social and economic problems of 
the country apart from this there has broke out a scandal the 
essence of which lies in that the former chief of the 
counterintelligence service has accused the leaders of the 
parliament and government of corruption and made public some 
compromising facts. Four month later P. Jasray had to refer to 
the court so that to succeed in getting "his dignity and honour 
violated to be restored". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

