<H3> <TI>   MSDP Backs Call for Government's Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MSDP Backs Call for Government's Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1504173294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1427 GMT 15 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1504173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Yesterday 
the Mongolian Social Democratic Party (MSDP) has officially 
announced their backing of the actions of political struggle 
being carried out by the Mongolian Democratic Association (MDA) 
and the Union of Mongolian Students (UMS) for resignation of the 
government. The political hunger strike by the members and 
supporters of the MDA and UMS held at the central square of the 
Mongolian capital is joined by the deputy chairman of the MSDP 
with one of his party member. 
  While the MSDP is joining the political struggle the stand 
of 
another parliamentary opposition party the Mongolian National 
Democratic Party (MNDP) was expressed by one of the leadership 
of the party through the national television saying that the 
MNDP regards the actions by the MDA and the UMS as a struggle 
for justice. 

</TEXT>

