<H3> <TI>   President Consults Leaders on Resignation Demands </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Consults Leaders on Resignation Demands </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1504174894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1439 GMT 15 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1504174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
Mongolian president is going on the top consultations starting a 
day ago in order to overcome the opposition arising in 
connection with the hunger strike and other actions for 
resignation of the goverment carried out by the Mongolian 
Democratic Association (MDA) at the central square of the 
Mongolian capital. Particiated in the consultations are leaders 
of the three parliamentary parties and the Prime Minister P. 
Jasray. During the meeting the sides have agreed to consider 
the political actions for resignation of the government on the 
part of the MDA as a subject under discussion at the Great State 
Hural and make public the social position of the parliamentary 
parties referring to the situation shaped down through their 
leaders, informs the press service of the Mongolian president. 

</TEXT>

