<F P=101> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Student Movement Accused of `Over-Politicization' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Student Movement Accused of `Over-Politicization' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1504182194 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1420 GMT 15 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1504182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- According 
to the public opinion poll conducted by the Movement for 
Renewing the Union of Mongolian Students (UMS) with embracing 
some 650 students from six largest universities and colleges of 
the country, the majority of them are accusing the UMS of 
over-politicization regarding its activities which does not 
correspond to its rules. The UMS is actively participating in 
the political struggle supporting the MDA [Mongolian Democratic 
Association] and other oppositional parties who is blaming the 
government for corruption and incompetence and stands for its 
resignation. The political situation in the country is becoming 
heated and lasting for three daylong is the hunger strike of a 
group of representatives of the opposition at the main square of 
the capital. The most of respondents are in favour of 
renovation of activities, structure and composition of the UMS 
considering the leadership of the organization fails to express 
and protect the fundamental interests of the student youth. 

</TEXT>

