<H3> <TI>   Poll Indicates Higher Income in Rural Areas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Indicates Higher Income in Rural Areas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1504175294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1433 GMT 15 Apr 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1504175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- According 
to the sociological poll conducted by the Statistical Department 
of the Chancellory of the Arhangay Aymag which covers some 50 
city and rural families totaling 254 people, the monthly income 
of a family in the city is 22.9 thousand tugrik while in the 
countryside 29.8 thousand tugrik. For the first time the income 
of the countryfolk has increased that of the city residents 
which is due to the privatization of cattle carried out in the 
countryside. The standard level is higher in the countryside 
but the structure of the foodstuffs does not meet to 
physiological normatives. For example the consumption of meat, 
rice, porridges, sweets, vegetables and butter and vegetable oil 
per one rural person is lower the required standards by from 30 
per cent to 2 fold. But the consumption of flour and bakeries 
is higher and as for milk and dairy produce is quite near the 
standards. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

