  [Text] Malaysia is a gateway to ASEAN with the 350 million 
people in its dynamic region. The country is also a gateway to 
the whole of the East Asia region. The minister of 
international trade and industry, Datuk Sri Rafidah Aziz said in 
view of this there should be a greater network between the 
private sectors of both Malaysia and Czech. She noted that 
Malaysia is very interested to receive foreign direct 
investments in a broad range of activities. She said this at a 
meeting with the Foreign Minister of Czech Josef Zieleniec and 
his 35-member trade delegation at her ministry in Kuala Lumpur 
today. 
  Datuk Sri Rafidah said bilateral trade of the two countries 
was only U.S.$20 million last year. She pointed out that the 
volume is very small and there is potential to expand it. 
  Mr. Josef Zieleniec and the delegation are on a two-day 
visit 
to Malaysia. He called on the minister of foreign affairs, 
Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi, at the Foreign Ministry in Kuala 
Lumpur this afternoon. 

