<H3> <TI>   Peacekeeping Troops To Remain in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peacekeeping Troops To Remain in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904072594 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0558 GMT 19 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, April 19 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- Malaysia 
will not withdraw its troops serving with the United Nations 
Protection Force (Unprofor) in Bosnia-Herzegovina despite the 
government's apprehension over the situation there, Prime 
Minister Dr Mahathir Mohamed said Tuesday. The government 
cannot recall its troops because the move will be similar to the 
measures of the United Nations which we criticise, he said when 
asked to comment on the latest situation in Bosnia. 
  The government is aware of the dangers faced by our soldiers 
but we cannot allow the Bosnians to be killed just like that by 
the Serbs, he told a news conference after presenting excellence 
service awards to Home Ministry staff at the Prime Minister's 
Department, here. 
  The prime minister said the government was concerned over 
the 
Malaysian soldiers because they were not equipped with adequate 
weapons as their duty was only peacekeeping. 
  He also said that if the Malaysian soldiers were entrapped, 
he feared that the other UN soldiers might not go to their 
assistance as was the case when the Bosnians needed help. 
  Dr Mahathir said that even so, the government would not 
withdraw the 1,500 Malaysian soldiers, most of them from the 
23rd Battalion Royal Malay Regiment stationed in several Bosnian 
towns including Sarajevo, because the government did not only 
speak of justice but also practised it. 
  Earlier, he criticised the [words indistinct] and the 
Security Council for not doing anything to help the Muslims in 
Goradze. 
  He said that they were actually not interested to help and 
purposely allow the Serbs to kill the Bosnians and occupy the 
town. 
  When the Serbs advanced, they did not put a stop to it and 
now they are merely saving the UN troops and leaving the Muslims 
without any help, he said. 

</TEXT>

