<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Philippine Embassy in Kuala Lumpur should 
explain to its people the real situation relating to the 
rounding up of more than 1,000 Philippine workers at St. John 
Cathedral in the federal capital on March the 27th. Deputy Home 
Minister Datuk Megat Junid Megat Ayub said the Philippines 
should understand Malaysia's position and the problems it faced 
following influx of illegal workers. 
  Speaking to reporters at parliament house, he said if the 
embassy wants the issue to be settled amicably, then they should 
tell the Philippine people that the operation was carried out in 
accordance with the law. He said Malaysians, too, (?were 
arrested) overseas for overstaying, but the government did not 
protest. Datuk Megat Junid said Malaysia was facing not only 
the problem of illegal workers from the Philippines, but from 
other countries like Indonesia, Bangladesh, Thailand, and 
Myanmar [Burma] as well. 

