<H3> <TI>   Weapons Found in Seized Vietnamese Trawlers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Weapons Found in Seized Vietnamese Trawlers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904092994 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0402 GMT 19 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, April 19 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- The marine 
police Monday found two assault rifles and a grenade launcher in 
a Vietnamese fishing boat being detained at Cenderung fishing 
port in the east coast Trengganu state since March 7 for illegal 
fishing in Trengganu waters. 
  Marine Police officer Zainul Abidin Hassan said his men also 
recovered 97 rounds of rifle ammunition and 14 rounds of 
ammunition for the grenade launcher hidden in the boat. He said 
the marine police found the arms and ammunition, believed to be 
China-made, following a thorough inspection of the boat, which 
was detained by the Fisheries Department Marine Division. 
  All the 13 crew members of the boat were fined a total of 
[Malaysian ringgit] RM850000 (US$1=RM2.70) or 54 months' jail on 
March . They did not pay the fines. According to the Fisheries 
Department, no arms or amunitions were found on the boat at the 
time of arrest. 

</TEXT>

