<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh's Wife Appointed Head of Red Cross </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ranariddh's Wife Appointed Head of Red Cross </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904070394 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0400 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1904070394 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 19 Apr (AKP) -- The first meeting of the 
Kingdom of Cambodia's Red Cross Federation was organized last 
Monday at the Chaktomuk hall under the chairmanship of Samdech 
Chea Sim, chairman of the National Assembly. 
  The meeting decided to appoint Princess Norodom Marie 
Ranariddh, chairman of the Central Committee and Her Majesty 
Norodom Monineat Sihanouk, honorary chairman of the Cambodian 
Red Cross Federation. 
  On behalf of His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk, Samdech Chea Sim 
stressed that this meeting's objective is to set up the Red 
Cross Federation by grouping the country's three Red Cross 
organizations: the Red Cross of the State of Cambodia, that of 
the National United Front for an Independent, Neutral, Peaceful, 
and Cooperative Cambodia (FUNCINPEC), and that of the Khmer 
People's National Liberation Front (KPNLF). 
  The Cambodian Red Cross Federation was recognized on 24 
March 
1994 among member countries of the Red Cross and of the Red 
Crescent. 
  The federation has seven basic principles, taken from the 
ICRC (International Committee of the Red Cross), including 
humanitarian action, justice, neutrality, and independence. 
  The National Assembly Chairman expects that the executive 
committee of the federation would forge good relations with 
international circles in order to respond to the Cambodian 
people's needs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

