<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Press Reports on Fighting in Pailin Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Press Reports on Fighting in Pailin Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    SRV Troops Hired To Attack Pailin </H4>

<F P=102> BK1704084294 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1704084294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the revelation by six soldiers of the 
two- headed government captured on 13 and 14 April, the 
government used foreign financial aid for national 
reconstruction to hire 500 (Dac Cong) commando troops, selected 
from the communist Vietnamese's 7th, 9th, 330th, and 309th 
Divisions, to attack Pailin. The soldiers were paid $100 daily. 
  These Vietnamese soldiers were used to fight in Cambodia 
before and some of them even used to be posted in Pailin. They 
can say some Cambodian words and have dressed up as Khmer Royal 
Armed Forces troops. They are front line forces. Somehow, in 
their onslaught on Pailin, 300 of them were killed or wounded in 
just a few days. Now, the remaining 200 soldiers are stationed 
at Kaong Kang Monastery and Phnum Yat adjoining Pailin town. 
  Although the Vietnamese soldiers are front line intervention 
forces, the Pailin battlefield situation has so far caused them 
to prepare for hasty retreat. 
  These actions are evidence that the two-headed government, 
communist Vietnamese, and the alliance have used national 
coffers to wage war. And they have gone so far as to hire the 
communist Vietnamese troops to destroy the Cambodian nation and 
people mercilessly. The nation and people are resolved to 
oppose the two-headed government, which has sold the nation out 
and destroyed the nation and people, and its masters until 
genuine peace is restored to Cambodia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

