Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dissident Camp Protests Secretary Perry's Trip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dissident Camp Protests Secretary Perry's Trip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1904083594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0827 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 19 (YONHAP) -- Nearly 30 members of 
Chongukyonhap, an alliance of dissident activists for "democracy 
and national unification," demonstrated in front of the U.S. 
Embassy in central Seoul Tuesday morning to protest U.S. Defense 
Secretary William Perry's visit. 
  They delivered to the American Embassy a letter addressed to 
Perry, accusing Washington of "intentionally aggravating" 
tension on the Korean peninsula to benefit the U.S. defense 
industry and to sustain its world hegemony as the sole military 
power even though the Cold War is over. 
  They also called on Perry to drop his earlier remark warning 
of a war against North Korea, to withdraw immediately all 
Patriot missiles from South Korea and to suspend the "Team 
Spirit" military exercise permanently. 
  Meanwhile, Secretary Perry is slated to arrive here late 
Tuesday night, the Defense Ministry said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
